```json
{
"application": "Nextflow",
"details": {
"software": [
"Singularity",
"R",
"bedtools",
"STAR",
"samtools",
"umitools",
"manorm",
"ultraplex",
"multiqc",
"fastqc",
"fastq_screen",
"bowtie"
],
"resources": [
"CPU: 64",
"Memory: 350GB",
"Storage: 24GB LSCRATCH",
"Time: 18 hours"
],
"workflow": "iCLIP_Transcriptome_v3.1.0.nf"
}
}
```

The script uses Nextflow as the workflow manager. It also utilizes various bioinformatics tools like Singularity for containerization, R for statistical analysis, and several other tools for specific tasks in RNA sequencing analysis. The script allocates 64 CPU cores, 350 GB of memory, and 24 GB of temporary storage. It has a time limit of 18 hours for execution. The script utilizes the iCLIP_Transcriptome_v3.1.0.nf workflow.
